obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (57390)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57390&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 4th April, 2021.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (57391)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57391&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "Chairperson" includes Chairperson, Chairman, President and Presiding Officer of a Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) "Member" includes Vice-Chairman, Vice-Chairperson, Vice-President, Account Member,`
  line `Administrative Member, Judicial Member, Expert Member, Law Member, Revenue Member and`
  line `Technical Member of a Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(c) "notified date" means the 4th April, 2021;`
  line
  line `(d) "Schedule" means the Schedule appended to this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "Tribunal" means a Tribunal, Appellate Tribunal or Authority as specified in column (2) of`
  line `the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (57357)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Qualifications, appointment, etc., of Chairperson and Members of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57357&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, order or decree of any court, or in any law for the`
  line `time being in force, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to`
  line `provide for the qualifications, appointment, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and other`
  line `conditions of service of the Chairperson and Member of a Tribunal after taking into consideration the`
  line `experience, specialisation in the relevant field and the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has not completed the age of fifty years shall not be eligible for`
  line `appointment as a Chairperson or Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and the Member of a Tribunal shall be appointed by the Central Government on`
  line `the recommendation of a Search-cum-Selection Committee constituted under sub-section (3), in such`
  line `manner as the Central Government may, by rules, provide.`
  line
  line `(3) The Search-cum-Selection Committee, except for the State Administrative Tribunal, shall consist`
  line of---
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, who shall be the Chief Justice of India or a Judge of Supreme Court nominated`
  line `by him;`
  line
  line `(b) two Members, who are Secretaries to the Government of India to be nominated by that`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(c) one Member, who ---`
  line
  line `(i) in case of appointment of a Chairperson of a Tribunal, shall be the outgoing Chairperson`
  line `of that Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of appointment of a Member of a Tribunal, shall be the sitting Chairperson of that`
  line `Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in case of the Chairperson of the Tribunal seeking re-appointment, shall be a retired`
  line `Judge of the Supreme Court or a retired Chief Justice of a High Court, to be nominated by the`
  line `Chief Justice of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the following cases, such Member shall always be a retired Judge of the`
  line `Supreme Court or a retired Chief Justice of a High Court, to be nominated by the Chief Justice of`
  line `India, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) Industrial Tribunal constituted by the Central Government under the Industrial`
  line `Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947);`
  line
  line `(ii) Debt Recovery Tribunal and Debt Recovery Appellate Tribunal established under the`
  line `Recovery of Debts and Bankruptcy Act, 1993 (51 of 1993);`
  line
  line `(iii) where the Chairperson or the outgoing Chairperson, as the case may be, of a Tribunal`
  line `is not a retired Judge of the Supreme Court or a retired Chief Justice or Judge of a High`
  line `Court; and`
  line
  line `(iv) such other Tribunals as may be notified by the Central Government, in consultation`
  line `with the Chairperson of the Search-cum Selection Committee of that Tribunal; and`
  line
  line `(d) the Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry or Department under which the`
  line `Tribunal is constituted or established--Member-Secretary:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Search-cum-Selection Committee for a State Administrative Tribunal shall`
  line `consist of---`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Justice of the High Court of the concerned State---Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Secretary of the concerned State Government---Member;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chairman of the Public Service Commission of the concerned State---Member;`
  line
  line `(d) one Member, who---`
  line
  line `(i) in case of appointment of a Chairman of the Tribunal, shall be the outgoing Chairman`
  line `of the Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of appointment of a Member of the Tribunal, shall be the sitting Chairman of`
  line `the Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in case of the Chairman of the Tribunal seeking re-appointment, shall be a retired`
  line `Judge of a High Court nominated by the Chief Justice of the High Court of the concerned`
  line `State:`
  line
  line `Provided that such Member shall always be a retired Judge of a High Court nominated by the`
  line `Chief Justice of the High Court of the concerned State, if the Chairperson or the outgoing`
  line `Chairperson of the State Administrative Tribunal, as the case may be, is not a retired Chief Justice`
  line `or Judge of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(e) the Secretary or the Principal Secretary of the General Administrative Department of the`
  line `concerned State---Member-Secretary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson of the Search-cum-Selection Committee shall have the casting vote.`
  line
  line `(5) The Member-Secretary of the Search-cum-Selection Committee shall not have any vote.`
  line
  line `(6) The Search-cum-Selection Committee shall determine the procedure for making its`
  line recommendations.
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, order or decree of any court, or in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, the Search-cum-Selection Committee shall recommend a panel of two`
  line `names for appointment to the post of Chairperson or Member, as the case may be, and the Central`
  line `Government shall take a decision on the recommendations made by that Committee, preferably`
  line `within three months from the date of such recommendation.`
  line
  line `(8) No appointment shall be invalid merely by reason of any vacancy or absence of a Member in`
  line `the Search-cum-Selection Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (57358)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Removal of Chairperson or Member of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57358&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, on the`
  line `recommendation of the Committee, remove from office, in such manner as may be provided by rules, any`
  line `Chairperson or a Member, who---`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as such Chairperson or Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `such Chairperson or Member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Chairperson or Member is proposed to be removed on any ground specified`
  line `in clauses (c) to (e), he shall be informed of the charges against him and given an opportunity of being`
  line `heard in respect of those charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (57359)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and Member of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57359&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in any judgment, order or decree of any court, or in any law for the time being in force,---`
  line
  line `(i) the Chairperson of a Tribunal shall hold office for a term of four years or till he attains the age`
  line `of seventy years, whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Member of a Tribunal shall hold office for a term of four years or till he attains the age of`
  line `sixty-seven years, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a Chairperson or Member is appointed between the 26th day of May, 2017 and`
  line `the notified date, and the term of his office or the age of retirement specified in the order of appointment`
  line `issued by the Central Government is greater than that which is specified in this section, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the term of office or age of retirement or both, as the`
  line `case may be, of the Chairperson or Member shall be as specified in his order of appointment, subject to a`
  line `maximum term of office of five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (57360)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Eligibility for re-appointment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57360&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson and Member of a Tribunal shall be eligible`
  line `for re-appointment in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in making such re-appointment, preference shall be given to the service rendered by`
  line `such person.`
  line
  line `(2) All re-appointments shall be made in the same manner as provided in sub-section (2) of section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (57361)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Salary and allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57361&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, order or`
  line `decree of any court, or in any law for the time being in force, and without prejudice to the generality of`
  line `the foregoing power, the Central Government may make rules to provide for the salary of the Chairperson`
  line `and Member of a Tribunal and they shall be paid allowances and benefits to the extent as are admissible`
  line `to a Central Government officer holding the post carrying the same pay:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the Chairperson or Member takes a house on rent, he may be reimbursed a house rent`
  line `higher than the house rent allowance as are admissible to a Central Government officer holding the post`
  line `carrying the same pay, subject to such limitations and conditions as may be provided by rules.`
  line
  line `(2) Neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson`
  line `or Member of the Tribunal may be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (57362)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Amendment of Act 14 of 1947.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57362&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `In section 7D of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947, for the words`
  line `and figures “Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), be governed by the provisions`
  line `of the section 184 of that Act”, the words and figures “the Tribunal Reforms Act, 2021, be governed by`
  line `the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act” shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (57363)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Amendment of Act 37 of 1952.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57363&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `In the Cinematograph Act, 1952,---`
  line
  line `(a) in section 2, clause (h) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(b) in section 5C,---`
  line
  line `(i) for the word "Tribunal", at both the places where it occurs, the words "High Court" shall`
  line `be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) sub-section (2) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(c) sections 5D and 5DD shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(d) in section 6, the words and brackets "or, as the case may be, decided by the Tribunal (but not`
  line `including any proceeding in respect of any matter which is pending before the Tribunal)" shall be`
  line omitted;
  line
  line `(e) in sections 7A and 7C, for the word "Tribunal", wherever it occurs, the words "High Court"`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(f) in sections 7D, 7E and 7F, the words "the Tribunal,", wherever they occur, shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(g) in section 8, in sub-section (2), clauses (h), (i), (j) and (k) shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (57364)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Amendment of Act 14 of 1957.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57364&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `In the Copyright Act, 1957,---`
  line
  line `(a) in section 2,---`
  line
  line `(i) clause (aa) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(ii) clause (fa) shall be re-lettered as clause (faa) and before the clause (faa) as so re-lettered,`
  line `the following clause shall be inserted, namely:---`
  line
  line `'(fa) "Commercial Court", for the purposes of any State, means a Commercial Court`
  line `constituted under section 3, or the Commercial Division of a High Court constituted under`
  line `section 4, of the Commercial Courts Act, 2015 (4 of 2016);';`
  line
  line `(iii) for clause (u), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `'(u) "prescribed" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to proceedings before a High Court, prescribed by rules made by the`
  line `High Court; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in other cases, prescribed by rules made under this Act;';`
  line
  line `(b) in section 6,---`
  line
  line `(i) for the words "Appellate Board", wherever they occur, the words "Commercial Court"`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) the words and figures "constituted under section 11 whose decision thereon shall be final"`
  line `shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(c) in Chapter II, in the Chapter heading, the words "AND APPELLATE BOARD" shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(d) sections 11 and 12 shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(e) in sections 19A, 23, 31, 31A, 31B, 31C, 31D, 32, 32A and 33A, for the words "Appellate`
  line `Board", wherever they occur, the words "Commercial Court" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(f) in section 50, for the words "Appellate Board", wherever they occur, the words "High Court"`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(g) in section 53A,---`
  line
  line `(i) for the words "Appellate Board", wherever they occur, the words "Commercial Court"`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2), the words "and the decision of the Appellate Board in this behalf shall`
  line `be final" shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(h) in section 54, for the words "Appellate Board", the words "Commercial Court" shall be`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(i) for section 72, the following section shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"72. Appeals against orders of Registrar of Copyrights.---(1) Any person aggrieved by any`
  line `final decision or order of the Registrar of Copyrights may, within three months from the date of`
  line `the order or decision, appeal to the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such appeal shall be heard by a single Judge of the High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such Judge may, if he so thinks fit, refer the appeal at any stage of the`
  line `proceeding to a Bench of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an appeal is heard by a single Judge, a further appeal shall lie to a Bench of the`
  line `High Court within three months from the date of decision or order of the single Judge.`
  line
  line `(4) In calculating the period of three months provided for an appeal under this section, the`
  line `time taken in granting a certified copy of the order or record of the decision appealed against shall`
  line `be excluded.";`
  line
  line `(j) in sections 74 and 75, the words "and the Appellate Board", wherever they occur, shall be`
  line omitted;
  line
  line `(k) in section 77, the words "and every member of the Appellate Board" shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(l) in section 78, in sub-section (2),---`
  line
  line `(i) clauses (cA) and (ccB) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (f), the words "and the Appellate Board" shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (57365)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Amendment of Act 43 of 1961.`
