obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `In the Control of National Highways (Land and Traffic) Act,`
  line 2002,---
  line
  line `(a) in section 2,--`
  line
  line `(i) clause (a) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(ii) after clause (d), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:---`
  line
  line `'(da) "Court" means the principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction in a district, and`
  line `includes the High Court in exercise of its ordinary original civil jurisdiction;';`
  line
  line `(iii) clause (l) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(b) in Chapter II, in the Chapter heading, the words "AND TRIBUNALS, ETC." shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(c) section 5 shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(d) for section 14, the following section shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"14.Appeal.--- An appeal from any order passed, or any action taken, excluding issuance or serving of`
  line `notices, under sections 26, 27, 28, 36, 37 and 38 by the Highway Administration or an officer`
  line `authorised on its behalf, as the case may be, shall lie to the Court.";`
  line
  line `(e) sections 15 and 16 shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(f) in section 17, for the word "Tribunal", at both the places where it occurs, the word "Court"`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(g) section 18 shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(h) in section 19, for the word "Tribunal", at both the places where it occurs, the word "Court"`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(i) section 40 shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(j) in section 41,---`
  line
  line `(i) the words "or every order passed or decision made on appeal under this Act by the`
  line `Tribunal" shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(ii) the words "or Tribunal" shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(k) in section 50, in sub-section (2), clause (f) shall be omitted.`
