obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (57385)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to amend the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57385&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do, it may, by notification published in the Official Gazette, amend the Schedule and`
  line `thereupon, the said Schedule shall be deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament as soon as may be after it is issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (57386)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Rules to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57386&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the`
  line `rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (57387)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57387&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being`
  line `in force, any person appointed as the Chairperson or Chairman or President or Presiding Officer or`
  line `Vice-Chairperson or Vice-Chairman or Vice-President or Member of the Tribunal, Appellate Tribunal, or,`
  line `as the case may be, other Authorities specified in the Second Schedule and holding office as such`
  line `immediately before the notified date, shall, on and from the notified date, cease to hold such office, and`
  line `he shall be entitled to claim compensation not exceeding three months' pay and allowances for the`
  line `premature termination of term of his office or of any contract of service.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the Tribunals, Appellate Tribunals and other Authorities`
  line `specified in the Second Schedule appointed on deputation, before the notified date, shall, on and from the`
  line `notified date, stand reverted to their parent cadre, Ministry or Department.`
  line
  line `(3) Any appeal, application or proceeding pending before the Tribunal, Appellate Tribunal or other`
  line `Authorities specified in the Second Schedule, other than those pending before the Authority for Advance`
  line `Rulings under the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), before the notified date, shall stand transferred to`
  line `the court before which it would have been filed had this Act been in force on the date of filing of such`
  line `appeal or application or initiation of the proceeding, and the court may proceed to deal with such cases`
  line `from the stage at which it stood before such transfer, or from any earlier stage, or de novo, as the court`
  line `may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The balance of all monies received by, or advanced to, the Tribunal, Appellate Tribunal or other`
  line `Authorities specified in the Second Schedule and not spent by it before the notified date, shall, on and`
  line `from the notified date, stand transferred to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) All property of whatever kind owned by, or vested in, the Tribunal, Appellate Tribunal or other`
  line `Authorities specified in the Second Schedule before the notified date, shall stand transferred to, on and`
  line `from the notified date, and shall vest in the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (57388)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57388&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by general or special order published in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `such provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or`
  line `expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the notified`
  line date.
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (57389)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898&sectionId=57389&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00040_202133_1629961891898
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunals Reforms (Rationalisation and Conditions of Service)`
  line `Ordinance, 2021 is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the Cinematograph Act,`
  line `1952 (37 of 1952), the Copyright Act, 1957 (14 of 1957), the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), the Patents`
  line `Act, 1970 (39 of 1970), the Airports Authority of India Act, 1994 (55 of 1994), the Trade Marks Act,`
  line `1999 (47 of 1999), the Geographical Indications of Goods (Registration and Protection) Act, 1999 (48 of`
  line `1999), the Protection of Plant Varieties and Farmers' Rights Act, 2001 (53 of 2001) and the Control of`
  line `National Highways (Land and Traffic) Act, 2002 (13 of 2003), as amended by the said Ordinance, shall`
  line `be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of those Acts, as amended by`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
